import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Read the content as a text file to manually parse it
with open(file_path, 'r') as f:
    content = f.readlines()

# Process the lines to create a DataFrame
cleaned_data = []
for line in content[1:]:  # Skip header
    line = line.strip()  # Remove whitespace
    if line.count(',') == 1:  # Check for correct number of commas
        cleaned_data.append([float(value) for value in line.split(',')])

# Create a DataFrame from the cleaned data
df = pd.DataFrame(cleaned_data, columns=['x', 'y'])
df.dropna(inplace=True)  # Drop any NA values if present

# Perform Linear Regression
X = df[['x']]
y = df['y']
model = LinearRegression()
model.fit(X, y)

# Coefficients
slope = model.coef_[0]
intercept = model.intercept_

# Calculate the coefficient of determination (R^2)
r_squared = model.score(X, y)

# Now let's visualize the results
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.scatter(df['x'], df['y'], color='blue', label='Data Points')
plt.plot(df['x'], model.predict(X), color='red', label='Regression Line')
plt.title('Linear Regression')
plt.xlabel('x')
plt.ylabel('y')
plt.legend()
plt.grid()

# Display plot
plt.show()
